## Summary

Convert the `getBuildingSchema()` method in `SupabaseSchemaRepository` from the current Promise-based API to use `ResultAsync` pattern for better error handling consistency.

## Context

This is part of the ongoing effort to adopt consistent error handling patterns using the `neverthrow` library throughout the schema repository. PR #2685 has already converted the `getSchema()` method to use `ResultAsync`, but it still calls the old Promise-based methods internally, requiring complex `andThen` chaining.

## Current Implementation

```typescript
private async getBuildingSchema(designSessionId: string) {
  const { data: buildingSchema, error: buildingSchemaError } =
    await this.client
      .from('building_schemas')
      .select('id, initial_schema_snapshot')
      .eq('design_session_id', designSessionId)
      .single()

  if (buildingSchemaError || !buildingSchema) {
    return {
      data: null,
      error: buildingSchemaError
        ? { message: buildingSchemaError.message }
        : null,
    }
  }

  return { data: { buildingSchema }, error: null }
}
```

## Desired Implementation

```typescript
private getBuildingSchema(designSessionId: string): ResultAsync<{ buildingSchema: BuildingSchema }, Error> {
  return ResultAsync.fromPromise(
    this.client
      .from('building_schemas')
      .select('id, initial_schema_snapshot')
      .eq('design_session_id', designSessionId)
      .single(),
    (error) => new Error(`Failed to get building schema: ${String(error)}`)
  ).andThen(({ data: buildingSchema, error: buildingSchemaError }) => {
    if (buildingSchemaError || !buildingSchema) {
      return errAsync(new Error(buildingSchemaError?.message || 'Building schema not found'))
    }
    return okAsync({ buildingSchema })
  })
}
```

## Benefits

1. **Consistent Error Handling**: Aligns with the ResultAsync pattern used in `getSchema()`
2. **Simplified Calling Code**: Will allow `getSchema()` to have simpler `andThen` chaining
3. **Better Type Safety**: ResultAsync provides better compile-time error handling guarantees
4. **Improved Maintainability**: Consistent patterns across the codebase

## Related Files

- `frontend/internal-packages/agent/src/repositories/supabase.ts` (lines 136-154)
- `frontend/internal-packages/agent/src/repositories/types.ts` (interface updates may be needed)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `getBuildingSchema()` method returns `ResultAsync<{ buildingSchema }, Error>`
- [ ] All callers are updated to use the new ResultAsync API
- [ ] Error messages provide meaningful context
- [ ] Tests are updated to verify the new behavior
- [ ] Lint checks pass

## Related Issues

- Follows up on PR #2685 which converted `getSchema()` to ResultAsync
- Pairs with the refactoring of `getSchemaVersions()` for complete consistency

